 inserted into the centre of the cake comes out clean. Allow to cool in tin for 5 minutes, then turn out onto a wire rack. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place remaining 150 g chocolate into mixing bowl and melt <b>5 min\/50°C\/speed 2<b>."},{"content":"Place cake onto a serving plate and drizzle melted chocolate over cake."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Red wine pears"},{"content":"Place a frying pan over low heat. Place pears and sugar into a bowl and gently mix until pears are evenly coated in sugar. Place coated pears and sugar into frying pan and cook for 8-10 minutes, gently turning pears frequently to avoid burning. Turn frying pan up to medium heat. Add wine and continue to cook for approx. 6-10 minutes to form a syrup. Transfer cooked pears and syrup into the centre of cake. Serve cake with warm caramelised pears and whipped cream (optional)."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Buerr bosc pear, or other variety of brown skinned pear are preferable.","We used merlot in this recipe, but you can use any type of red wine.","You can serve this cake without the pears. Simply serve after step 6."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h 20m","16 slices"]}